main event: An unidentified aerial phenomenon was observed in Pori, Finland on September 20, 1963.
interesting points: The observation lasted several seconds and involved a spherical object with a fiery trail traveling from NW to SE,The object made no sound during the sighting,The Finnish Academy Professor evaluated the object as a meteor,Multiple possible evaluations included balloon, aircraft, astronomical meteor, and insufficient data,The report is part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFOs.
sighted object: spherical object with a fiery trail
